      textEn: [
        "Venice is a world-famous city on water. Its crisscrossing canals make small boats the main means of transport\u2014the equivalent of cars on a regular street.",
        "Venice\u2019s gondolas are twenty to thirty feet long, narrow and deep, somewhat like canoes. Their bows and sterns curve upward like a new moon hanging at the horizon. They move with light, agile grace, like water snakes in a ditch.",
        "We sat in the cabin on cushions soft as sofas. The boat passed under one stone bridge after another, each of different design. We opened the curtains and gazed at the ancient buildings towering on both banks, greeting passing boats\u2014an endless source of delight.",
        "The boatman\u2019s navigating skill was exceptional. The boat moved at great speed among heavy traffic, yet he handled it with perfect ease. No matter how crowded, he could always weave through. In the narrowest passages, he steered smoothly at full speed, even making sharp turns. Buildings on both sides flew past; our eyes could barely keep up, not knowing where to look.",
        "Merchants hurried off boats with large bundles of goods to do business along the river. Young women chatted and laughed aloud in the boats. Children accompanied by nannies rode boats to the countryside for fresh air. Elderly people brought their whole families to church by boat to pray.",
        "At midnight, the theater let out and a crowd surged onto their hired gondolas. The clustered boats soon dispersed, vanishing into the winding canals. From afar came laughter and farewells. The water surface grew quiet; only the moon\u2019s reflection swayed on the water. Tall stone buildings stood along the riverbanks, ancient bridges spanned the water, and boats of all sizes were moored at the docks. Silence enveloped this city on water, and ancient Venice sank once more into deep slumber."
      ],
